Comment: mwepcot82 said "The 1958 addition of the #GrandCanyonDiorama painted by artist Delmer J. Yoakum necessitated a change in the rolling stock as well; instead of facing forward, the new flatcars' benches now faced right so that the passengers could better enjoy the scenes. The diorama, which includes taxidermic animals (the only ones in the park) in lifelike poses, is the longest in the world. Painted on a single piece of seamless canvas and representing the view from the canyon's south rim, the rear of the diorama measures 306 feet (93 m) long, 34 feet (10 m) high and is covered with 300 gallons (1,100 L) of paint in 14 colors.[5] Animals that are included in the diorama include mule deer, mountain lion, desert bighorn sheep, golden eagle, wild turkeys, striped skunk and porcupine. A 96-year-old Hopi chief, Chief Nevangnewa, blessed the trains on the diorama's opening day. The cost was US$367,000, and it took 80,000 labor hours to construct. The main theme of Ferde GrofÃ©'s "On The Trail," the third movement from his Grand Canyon Suite, is piped in through the train's sound system as it enters the diorama."

Comment: mz_poeticmoodsz_muslimah said "'Uqbah bin 'Amir, may Allah be pleased with him, reported:

Allah's Messenger (may peace be upon him) one day went out and he offered the Prayer over the martyrs of Uhud just as the Prayer is offered over the dead. He then came back and sat on the pulpit and said: I will be the predecessor before you. I will be your witness and, by Allah,I perceive as if I am seeing with my own eyes my Hawd (River in Paradise) at this very moment and I have been given the keys of the treasures of the earth or the keys of the earth and, by Allah, I am not afraid that you might associate anything (with Allah after me), but I am afraid that you will be vying with one another (for the possession of) the treasures of the earth.

Chapter regarding grant of Ghuyub (Unseen) to Prophet (Peace be upon him) and of things which have to happen in future.

The hadiths on this subject are like a #vast #ocean, the #depth of which #cannot be #found and the #water of which #cannot #end. This is one aspect of his miracles which is "DEFINITELY KNOWN" We have many hadiths which have reached us by multiple paths of transmission (tawatur) which prove that the Prophet (Alayhi salaatu wa sallam) has been given knowledge of Unseen. It is narrated by Hudhayfa (radiAllaahuanahu) that the Messenger of Allah (Alayhi salaatu wa sallam) stood on his (Pulpit) and "HE DID NOT LEAVE OUT ANYTHING BUT EXPLAINED WHAT SHALL HAPPEN UNTIL THE LAST HOUR" Whoever remembered it remembered it and whoever forgot it forgot it.[Qadhi Iyaad's Ash-Shifa, Volume No.1, Page No. 206]

Comment: littlearabiadistrict said "Enjoy the â€ª#â€Kabobâ€¬ at @elmahroosacafe!

According to Sevan NiÅŸanyan, an etymologist of the Turkish language, the word kabob is derived from the Persian word "kabap" meaning "fry". The word was first mentioned in a Turkish script of Kyssa-i Yusuf in 1377, which is the oldest known source where kebab is mentioned as a food. However, he emphasizes that the word has the equivalent meaning of "frying/burning" with "kabÄbu" in the old Akkadian language, and "kbabÄ/×›×‘×‘×" in Syriac language. Tradition has it that the dish was invented by medieval Persian soldiers who used their swords to grill meat over open-field fires."

Comment: micahmthenson said "|| Dreams Do Come True || Once upon a time there was a little girl, and this little girl had a dream to be something that didn't exist. She knew her that her dream was virtually impossible but that is why it is called a dream, it is an idea or vision of something wanted so terribly but it is completely out of reach. However even though years went by the dream it did not die. It was locked away in the deepest part of her innocent young hopeful heart. One day she decided to get a job at the happiest place on earth. Since she could not be exactly what she dreamed of being, she at least wanted to feel apart of the magical memories that she loved so much as a child. Once she went into the building she saw the first preview for the movie 'Princess and the Frog' At that moment her heart stopped! A dream that she had tucked away in the farthest part of her heart was now a reality. Not only was the princess her same skin color but the princess literally looked like a cartoon replica of the young girl. To tie this story all together, just because you have a dream that is impossible and others may laugh at what you cry out to God for, this does not mean it can not happen. Every single great innovator, visionary, or leader in history all had dreams and goals that were impossible and completely out of reach. But the moral of this story is if you have something in your heart do not give up on it, push in, try harder, and trust that God hears your prayers and sees the cry's of your heart. Because just like this young girl, her dream was impossible but one day her dream became a reality and she seized that moment the instant it became possible! Do not be discouraged, be hopeful, dream bigger, and know that one day you will have your hearts desire!  In the words of Mr. Walt Disney, "All our dreams can come true, if we have the courage to pursue them" -Live in Truth- 
Micah Henson

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/27
Function:  Targeted Removal
Rating:  5/10

Let's start with the negative; you're trading 4/4 flyers with whatever you're targeting so time this card very carefully.  That being said, this card EXILES multiple creatures whenever you damn well feel like it.  This card is great for situations when you'd rather face off against 4/4 flyers rather than a Vorinclex or Prophet of Kruphix.  It doesn't exactly put you in a better position, just a more palatable one.  This works great with cards that can repeatedly return things to their owner's hands since tokens just disappear. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/28
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  8/10

Grave Pact has been a powerhouse for years and it has been improved in two ways:  First and foremost it has flash with makes for some really painful ambush plays to really punish your opponents.  2nd the cost only requires BB to Grave Pact's BBB although the CMC has increased by 1.  Decks with finely tuned mana bases won't see the difference but everyone else will appreciate the lower black requirement.

#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/28
Function:  Misc./Kinda sorta mass removal with impeccable timing
Rating:  3/10

I want to talk about this card in its best environment at its most power.  This card shines in monoblue or in the presence of Stormtide Leviathan.  You have to have access to flash with Winding Canyons or Teferi, Mage of Zhalfir because playing it on your turn gives the opponents the opportunity to replaying everything immediately after your turn with all the triggered abilities.  When it is played with flash it is almost comparable with Cyclonic Rift in terms of devastating reach.  If you have access to Deadeye Navigator no one will be able to have any creatures stick to the battlefield. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/27
Function:  Targeted Removal
Rating:  5/10

Let's start with the negative; you're trading 4/4 flyers with whatever you're targeting so time this card very carefully.  That being said, this card EXILES multiple creatures whenever you damn well feel like it.  This card is great for situations when you'd rather face off against 4/4 flyers rather than a Vorinclex or Prophet of Kruphix.  It doesn't exactly put you in a better position, just a more palatable one.  This works great with cards that can repeatedly return things to their owner's hands since tokens just disappear. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  8/10

Grave Pact has been a powerhouse for years and it has been improved in two ways:  First and foremost it has flash with makes for some really painful ambush plays to really punish your opponents.  2nd the cost only requires BB to Grave Pact's BBB although the CMC has increased by 1.  Decks with finely tuned mana bases won't see the difference but everyone else will appreciate the lower black requirement.

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/28
Function:  Misc./Kinda sorta mass removal with impeccable timing
Rating:  3/10

I want to talk about this card in its best environment at its most power.  This card shines in monoblue or in the presence of Stormtide Leviathan.  You have to have access to flash with Winding Canyons or Teferi, Mage of Zhalfir because playing it on your turn gives the opponents the opportunity to replaying everything immediately after your turn with all the triggered abilities.  When it is played with flash it is almost comparable with Cyclonic Rift in terms of devastating reach.  If you have access to Deadeye Navigator no one will be able to have any creatures stick to the battlefield. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/02
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  6/10

I absolutely love this card; the title is so appropriate when you time this correctly.
I never cared much for Mindslaver unless you sacrificed it the same turn you played it which brings its total cost to 10.  I hate playing the Mindslaver and letting it sit around to be destroyed by other players and turning everyone against you out of paranoia.  The 8 CMC is better than Mindslaver's 10 for immediate use. Because it is a sorcery it can be copied so it can harm or help you.  This card is for patient, plotting masterminds who can wait for the perfect opportunity to turn someone's card against themself (Necropotence, Greater Good) or to gain an ally against their will. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/02
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  4/10

This card is the epitome of a double-edged sword.  Just make sure your damage output is always higher than your opponents or else you'll be in big trouble.  The flash ability gives you a lot of reach because your opponents can't account for damage that they can't see on the battlefield.  This card is also amazing in conjunction with white protection spells like Righteous Aura or Solitary Confinement.  You can just sit pretty in one corner and watch the world burn.

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/02
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  4/10

This card is the epitome of a double-edged sword.  Just make sure your damage output is always higher than your opponents or else you'll be in big trouble.  The flash ability gives you a lot of reach because your opponents can't account for damage that they can't see on the battlefield.  This card is also amazing in conjunction with white protection spells like Righteous Aura or Solitary Confinement.  You can just sit pretty in one corner and watch the world burn. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/02
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  6/10

I absolutely love this card; the title is so appropriate when you time this correctly.
I never cared much for Mindslaver unless you sacrificed it the same turn you played it which brings its total cost to 10.  I hate playing the Mindslaver and letting it sit around to be destroyed by other players and turning everyone against you out of paranoia.  The 8 CMC is better than Mindslaver's 10 for immediate use. Because it is a sorcery it can be copied so it can harm or help you.  This card is for patient, plotting masterminds who can wait for the perfect opportunity to turn someone's card against themself (Necropotence, Greater Good) or to gain an ally against their will. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/01
Function:  Targeted Removal
Rating:  8/10

This is a great card that rewards you for building up your supply of mana.  Instant speed exile is devastating to powerful decks because they generally contain powerful recursion cards to replay creatures from the graveyard.  Unless your opponents play with Pull From Eternity of Riftsweeper, your targets will remain gone for good.

#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"
